text: Shuyak Island State Park is an approximately 47,000 acre Alaska state park on most of Shuyak Island in the Kodiak Archipelago. The park includes a coastal forest of Sitka spruce, coastline, beaches, and waterways. The park contains four cabins for recreational use and is only accessible via air or water. ==References== Category:State parks of Alaska Category:Protected areas of Kodiak Island Borough, Alaska
title: Shuyak Island State Park
